      comment:
        "\u003cp\u003eThe tour was pretty much perfect in every kind of way. The meeting point was easy to navigate and find, and the staff were very professional on arrival. Our guide was friendly, clear and had a lot of knowledge which she shared with the group very well. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Vatican museums are absolutely huge, and I feel that without a tour, you would end up needing an entire day to have a look round. The tour was good in this sense as it focused on the highlights, but didn't feel too rushed at any point. If you are someone who wants to really take their time in the museums, and look around at everything, a tour isn't for you. The tour lasted 3 hours and concluded in St Peter's Basilica, where you will have a quick tour and then be allowed to free roam. It's possible to visit St Peter's square very easily after the tour finishes. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eMy only slight complaint is that they should invest in better headsets. If you were too far away from the guide, it would either become very muffled or cut off entirely.\u003c/p\u003e",
